      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "66657d5756ea164f",
      "text": "This does not mean that opacity must be dealt with in time, i.e. at datable points in time. That goes without saying. Rather, our assumption is that the solution lies in the way in which time differences are used. Temporalization here means: creating the difference between past and future."
